captions.text:
>>DON'T WORRY BABE.
MY PARENTS ARE GOING TO LOVE YOU.

YEAH, JUST COME OVER HERE AND MEET THEM.
ALL RIGHT.

OKAY.
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

BYE.
[DOORBELL] >>HELLO LITTLE BROTHER.

>>WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
I HAVE MOM AND DAD TONIGHT.

>>I JUST WANTED TO MEET YOUR WOMAN BRO-HAM.
>>FINE, BUT YOU BETTER BE REALLY NICE TO HER

AND TO ME.
OTHERWISE, YOU'VE GOT TO GO.

>>DO YOU WANT ME TO MAKE LIKE A TREE AND LEAVES?
>>YOU DONE?

>>GET IT?
BECAUSE OF THE LEAVES.

>>YEAH, THAT DOESN'T...
>>MOTHER.

>>MY FAVORITE SON!
GIVE YOUR MOTHER A KISS.

>>MWAH!
>>YOUR FATHER WILL BE SO HAPPY.

CHRIS?
CHRIS.

>>TRISH?
WHAT IS IT TRISH?

>>CHRIS, PUT DOWN THAT WHISK AND GET IN HERE.
>>TRISH YOUR WISH LIST IS FISCALLY IRRESPONSIBLE.

MY FAVORITE SON.
>>HEY.

[LAUGHTER] HEY, UH, MOTHER,
I BROUGHT YOU A GIFT.

>>OH!
>>DO YOU REALIZE WHAT THIS IS?

>>HIBISCUS?
>>YES.

I ATE LIKE FIVE OF THEM.
>>MITCH?

MITCH?
WHERE'S MITCH?

>>MOM, DAD DIED FIVE YEARS AGO.
>>OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

MITCH DIED IN A DITCH.
AND NOW HE'S THE GOT THE POST-MORTEMS.

>>GRANNY MADE HER FAMOUS LOBSTER BISQUE.
>>[CHEERING] >>WHO DO YOU ALWAYS HAVE TO

MAKE HIS FAVORITE EVEN TONIGHT?
YOU KNOW I HATE BISQUE.

>>YOU ARE A DISGRACE TO THIS FAMILY.
>>YOU ARE AROUND BISQUE 24/7.

DON'T YOU EVER GET SICK OF THE STUFF?
>>DO YOU EVER GET SICK OF BREATHING?

[SCOFFING SOUNDS] >>TISK, TISK.
>>YEAH, GOLLY.

>>IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT SON.
WE DROPPED YOU ON YOUR HEAD AS A CHILD.

>>THAT'S RIGHT.
I WAS RUNNING A MARATHON WITH YOU IN MY ARMS

AND I TORE
MY MENISCUS AND TRIPPED.

SORRY IF IT MADE YOU SUCH A FISH OUT OF WATER.
>>WE PROBABLY SHOULDN'T OF HAD YOU LISTEN

TO ALL THAT
CLASSICAL MUSIC AS A CHILD.

>>YOU SHOULD HAVE LISTENED
TO LIMP BIZKIT LIKE ME.

>>YEAH.
>>THAT'S WHAT WE MADE ME SO SOCIABLE.

>>[LAUGHTER] SOCIABLE?
YEAH, HEY WAIT!

WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT
BLIND DATE THAT I SET YOU

UP ON WITH VERONICA?
>>VERONICA?

OH I GUESS THAT WAS HER NAME.
>>THAT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE TONIGHT.

WHAT HAPPENED?
>>I GOT DISTRACTED.

>>BEAUTIFUL.
>>AH!

TRICKY STITCH.
>>WHO WANTS TO PLAY A SUPER FUN GAME?

>>WHAT ARE WE PLAYING?
>>RISK.

>>YES, WELL I AM PRETTY
GOOD AT RISK, SO...

>>WELL AT LEAST THERE'S ONE
THING YOU'RE GOOD AT.

>>WHAT IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?
>>YOU'RE A LOSER.

>>OKAY.
JUST BECAUSE I DON'T OWN MY OWN BUSINESS

DOESN'T MEAN--
>>BISQUENESS.

>>I DID GRADUATE FROM HARVARD THIS YEAR IF
ANYONE REMEMBERS THAT.

>>YEAH, IN PS-PSYCHOLOGY.
>>NEUROSURGERY.

>>PS-PSYCHOLOGY, PS-SURGERY,
THEY'RE THE PS-SAME THING!

>>NO, THEY ARE NOT.
I ALSO TOOK THE HARVARD FOOTBALL TEAM TO FOUR

BOWLS
IN THE LAST FOUR YEARS.

SO...
>>AND HOW MANY BOWLS OF BISQUE DID I SELL

IN
THE LAST FOUR YEARS?

>>THOSE ARE NOT EVEN COMPARABLE.
>>6,266.

>>MITCH?
MITCH?

>>WE ARE SO PROUD OF YOU HONEY.
>>I KNOW.

IT'S JUST...
>>JUST WAIT UNTIL MY GIRLFRIEND GETS HERE

AND THEN YOU'LL BE PROUD
OF ME TOO.

>>WE ARE PROUD OF YOU.
>>WHY?

[DOORBELL] >>HEY!
EVERYONE THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND.

>>HELLO FAMILY OF STEPHEN, HI.
[SOUNDS OF GREETING]

>>IT IS MY PLEASURE TO MEET
YOU AND YOUR ACQUAINTANCES.

ACQUAINTANCES, YES, YES.
I BROUGHT A DELICIOUS DISH OF BISCUITS.

OH, OH.
I LEFT IT IN MY CIVIC.

[LAUGHTER] LET ME GET THEM.
I'LL BE BRISK.

OKEY DOKIE.
ALL RIGHT!

YEP.
>>SO, WHAT DO YOU GUYS THINK?

>>WELL, STEPHEN YOU FOUND A WEIRDO.
>>YEAH.
